Schemata (assets/libs/schemata.js) is part of the md-previewer project
itself. It is an in-house renderer authored as part of this repository and
is distributed under the same license as md-previewer.

The name "Schemata" is the Greek plural of σχῆμα ("figure / form /
template"), reflecting the family of structured-explanation diagrams the
module renders (matrix, flow, cycle, BMC, mandara, fishbone). Earlier
working titles (both withdrawn): "smartart" (collided with Microsoft's
SmartArt trademark) and "zukai" (avoided for naming consistency with the
sibling kataskeve module).

See the top-level LICENSE file for the applicable terms.
